<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870430-0137 </DOCNO><HL> Perpetual Savings Bank System</HL><DD> 04/30/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> PASB </IN><DATELINE> ALEXANDRIA, Va.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Perpetual Savings Bank said it agreed to develop with a regional food-business trade group a network of supermarket and convenience store automated tellers and money order terminals.    The new network is to be offered to 2,000 retailers in Virginia, Maryland, Delaware, Washington and southern New Jersey. The thrift institution aims to have 120 automated tellers installed in the next 16 months and 200 money-order terminals in the next year.    Its partner in the venture is the Mid-Atlantic Food Dealers Association. </TEXT></DOC>